annotation.TEXT: So, I likely won't be able to point out any level design errors here, I don't think. However, if any of you know the SMB Special levels really well, and think you spot a discrepancy, let me know and I'll investigate it further.
Sorry that there isn't much to say right now.
Yay, the victory fanfare from the first Final Fantasy!
No, I want that coin. Gimme that coin. I must have that coin.
Wait, that wasn't Rush! That was Tango! Neat!
The boomerang isn't helping here... It would've been better if I was downthrusting this multi-coin block from above.

The map difficulty will remain on Normal, and I believe I'll leave all the other options as they are, with everything being available, and the map skins and music being random. Oh, and I'll leave Tutorials on, and just speed through any messages we've already seen.
Aha! That was a tricky 1-up to reach.
So, here we go! Now, I'm not nearly as familiar with the SMB Special levels as I am with the original SMB levels.
Oh, found a hidden block.
Alright, let's go!
To be continued...
So many bricks!!! Where's my AWESOME SPREAD GUN when I need it?
Votes for Google to change the comments back: At least 221,637.
Alright, we've already seen all of this tutorial text, so I'll just quickly speed through it.
Oh, there's a star here too! I'm not missing this one!
D'oh. The invincibility star fell down the hole...
Did I check these pipes back here? Yeah, I checked them, and I couldn't enter them.
Whoa, a hidden block! ...Wait... Don't tell me... I did it again, didn't I?
Blah, blah. Enough talk! Have at you!

And it led to a 1-up! I might've missed that if I didn't happen to hit that hidden block with my sword beam. (Although, I probably would've found the 1-up anyway just by attacking the bricks themselves.)
So, I guess Roll is searching for Mega Man, eh?
Oh, I found another multi-coin block. Neat.
Hello, and welcome back to Super Mario Bros. Crossover!
Argh! I meant to slide under that flame, but I hit the jump button just before pressing down there. Okay, come on now. Don't make any more stupid mistakes!
And here's a bonus room. Gotta be careful of pits in here.
Got him! That slime Bot is history!
Ooh, a sword power up, but can I reach it?
How about the Whip Skeleton from Simon's skins? I hope I don't get boned from making this decision!
Alright, I've wasted enough time in here.

What? A bonus room in a castle? What is this madness?! Well, actually, SMB2J (The Lost Levels) did it first... Or, did it? I think 2J and Special were both released in 1986, but which one came first? (UPDATE: Turns out Special came out first, shortly before 2J.)
Goombas fall down the hole.
Now, as for who I'm using to begin with... Well, I only got 1 vote, and it was for Link's alt. skin Ralph, from Oracle of Ages.
And now I'm back to the game. So, who should I use next? I guess I'll pick an arbitrary skin that hasn't been used yet...
I'm getting plenty of hearts, which is nice. Also, I'm sure there's something good hidden in this setup!
Whoops! Did I just glitch into a brick there for a split-second? Should I report that on the Exploding Rabbit forums?
Cool, now I can fire charge shots.
Alright, we're up to Red Ring already. That's cool.
Interestingly, I don't automatically march towards the pipe. Instead I have to walk there myself. Ohh, but walking's hard...
Hey, it's Eddie! Are you gonna give me tons of energy, 1-ups, and E-tanks?
Yes, nailed it this time!
And I'm running low on time again. There might be something worth finding in those bricks, but I'm not gonna bother now.
I love those "BOMB" fireworks!
Yep, got it!
At this point I got interrupted by something in real life, so I had to pause the recording temporarily. This is why you'll hear the music skip here.
...Or four or five... Wow, it's a hidden block staircase!
I figured there was a power up there. SMB Special must've taken that brick setup straight from the original SMB.
I've seen some videos of the Special levels, and I even played an SMB hack consisting of SMB Special's levels long ago. However, those aren't ingrained into my brain like the original SMB levels are.
Bah. Missed the 6. Also, what the heck was with the choppy video there? Was HyperCam 2 acting up on me, or was the computer doing other random processes in the background? Who knows...
I'm leaving the tutorials on just in case I pick up a new power up or something that has an explanation tied to it that we haven't seen yet. (I'm sure there are some.)
Ooh, double shot. Now I can have two subweapons on the screen at once.
Hmm... How about... Shadow from Final Fantasy VI, which is one of Ryu's skins! I probably should've used him instead of Haggle Man in world 8-3 last time, but whatever. I'll use him now.
Yep. I once again went and reached something the hard way, only to later find out that there was a hidden block that would've let me reach it more easily. Oh, well.
Whoa. I was a little worried I'd get burned in that corner there, but I'm good.
Oh, yeah. And since I'm not nearly as knowledgeable about the Special levels, I'm likely to miss some secrets, so let me know if I miss anything really valuable.
And, I'll just make arbitrary picks for the rest of the characters I use in this episode.
Yes, now my bone whip is stronger!
So, which characters should I use for world 2? Place your votes now! Also, if I missed anything important in world 1 that you guys want me to show off, let me know!
Yep, I figured there'd be a hidden block or two or three there...
I honestly did not know that hidden coin block was there. I just arbitrarily swung my sword while jumping and happened to hit it.
Yes!
Uh, oh. Pipe's too tall to get on top of. Better call Rush.
Alright, now who's next?
I thought that maybe there was some secret behind the pipe. You never know... Also, moonwalking into the pipe like a boss.
Well, I may not have an AWESOME SPREAD GUN right now, but I feel like smashing a bunch of these bricks anyway!
Yeah, yeah. We already know how Mega Man works, and Roll is no different.
Oh, and I remember this double-pyramid of blocks as well.
Wow, I like how I can destroy whole chunks of bricks at once. It's no AWESOME SPREAD GUN, but it's still nice.
Alright, it's boss time, against... Ganon? ...With Dr. Mario's Fever music? Okay, sure, whatever! Now, I may not have a sword or silver arrows, but my Mega Buster should be all I need!
I can enter this one, though!
I've gotten some bomb pick ups, which is nice, but I almost never use them. (I have a feeling they'd be handy against Buzzy Beetles, though.)
Huh? An M-bag, like from SML2? What's that do? It looks like it just gives me 8000 points. Is that all it does? And was such an item in the original SMB Special? (Answer: Yes.)
Now, who should I play the castle with? I don't believe I've ever used Roll yet, so let's give her a turn!

Okay, now because of a mistake I made during my previous playthrough, we never actually saw Ryu's tutorial text from the game before. Yeah, I had annotated in what it said, but I'll let it show for several seconds again here.
Well, I guess Ralph for 1-1 it is then!
Wow, really? There was absolutely nothing to murder with that star! Are there really supposed to be no enemies, not even piranha plants, in this region? Can somebody double-check this?
I do remember these hidden coin blocks being there from my past SMB Special experiences.
Now, as for what I'm doing next, I got 1 vote to do the Hard maps of SMB, and 2 votes to do the SMB Special maps, so the Special maps win!
Wouldn't the player be stuck down there if they were completely out of Rush/Tango/Whatever energy, though? Well, if that happened, they were probably very wasteful and deserved to be stuck.
Well, anyway, I got this holy water, which might be handy for hitting enemies below me in the future. It consumes 1 heart to use.
Yay, the level up fanfare from Final Fantasy Adventure!
